By the way, Doctor, how about becoming a VIP? Take advantage of this cost-effective service and free up some of that budget for Rhodes Island!
These new arrivals were specifically picked out for the Operators of Rhodes Island. Hopefully the real products look like they do in these pictures... Ugh...
Here's the pack the Procurement Department prepared for you! Please take it! Well, it's from the Procurement Department and they need you to pay for it.
Are you going to give this outfit to Hibiscus yourself, Doctor?

There's an event going on at the cafeteria right now. Plenty of food and drinks, and they're even giving out prizes! These three are the favorites to win - who do you think stands the best chance?
Those girls sure were in a hurry to replicate their school clubroom... Think it's out of a sense of nostalgia? They must have made some great memories.

With this authentic L.G.D. office set, anyone can experience what it's like to be a police chief. You better take me in when nobody's looking!

These luxurious outfits were meticulously crafted by designers with no budget constraints. Perhaps next time, the Procurement Division will also try purchasing them up without considering the expense... Actually, forget it. Kalt'sit would get mad.
A house that gives you a view of the night like this would cost a fortune in Leithania. Luckily, you can achieve the same thing here at a fraction of the cost.
An outfit made from Grani's recollections. We tried to connect her with a designer to make this possible, and here are the fruits of that work.
Don't you hate it when you let a promotion slide by? I know that feeling all too well! Luckily for you, Doctor, you have another chance!
Oh, are you a Rhodes Island Operator? One pizza to Closure's room, please and thank you.
I have no idea which cities the 'Seven Cities' are supposed to be, but the food and drinks here are must-try. Good enough to convince me to leave this sunless den, *hic*...

tagWord.text: The Operators are still rehearsing. Want to go in and take a look?
The pristine beauty of the beach, the melody of the waves splashing against the coast - it's all waiting for you at the Siesta Beach Hut!

While away from the cities, outfit is everything. Looking good is one thing, but practicality matters more. Understood?
I heard that Yen people would decorate their rooms like this during festivals. Warfarin will definitely love everything being red.
If you like the outfits you wore when experiencing the escape game, you can visit me to purchase it.
Whislash treats the younger generation of her family with great care. I wish I had an aunt just like her.
Chernobog Core City is really dangerous. Why not spend a little for some peace of mind?
Good news, Doctor. Our old friend has agreed to give us a discount on targeted headhunting.
I heard that it's a paid gift from one of our friends. How generous of him!
Everyone's style is so unique... You're asking how I dressed before? Oh, that's a secret.
Please contribute for the sake of the children's happiness!
Healthy meals... they're not really for me. Though, there must be people who want them, right?
Going on a long and dangerous journey? Stop dallying and get some better clothes for the operators then. What do you think of these?
Oh? Not bad, not bad at all. Some of these designs can be directly integrated into Rhodes Island's safehouses.
A new package proposed by our collaboration partner has arrived! Aren't you dying to check it out?
Sometimes, it's good to have a more long-term vision. Long live public welfare!
I'm... still a little scared. That outfit does look really good on Saria though...
